1. *Držala* sam torbu u levoj ruci. (I was holding the bag in my left hand.)
2. Ona je *držala* predavanje o srpskoj književnosti. (She was giving a lecture on Serbian literature.)
3. *Držala* sam se za ruku sa svojim prijateljem dok smo se spuštali niz stepenice. (I was holding hands with my friend while we were going down the stairs.)
4. Nikada ne bih mogao da *držim* divlju mačku kao kućnog ljubimca. (I could never keep a wild cat as a pet.)
5. Kako možeš *držati* dijetu kad su ti svi ovi slatkiši oko tebe? (How can you stick to a diet when all these sweets are around you?)
6. Moja baka *drži* baštu punu lepih cveća. (My grandmother maintains a garden full of beautiful flowers.)
7. Kada su nas uhvatili, policija nas je *držala* u pritvoru tri dana. (When they caught us, the police held us in custody for three days.)
8. *Držao* je ruku na mom ramenu i rekao da će sve biti u redu. (He had his hand on my shoulder and said everything will be okay.)
9. Kako možeš *držati* ovaj restoran otvorenim sam? (How can you keep this restaurant running by yourself?)
10. Mislila sam da je sve izgubljeno, ali *držim* se nade. (I thought everything was lost, but I'm still holding onto hope.)